Now I'll build a beautiful interactive API docs page:
REST API for the Mentora mentorship platform. Test with Hoppscotch (hoppscotch.io) or any HTTP client.
Here's a complete guide to testing every endpoint in Hoppscotch (hoppscotch.io):

Setup First
Base URL: http://localhost:3000
Save your token after login — you'll paste it into every protected request as:
Header: Authorization
Value:  Bearer <paste_token_here>

1. Sign Up as a Parent
Method:  POST
URL:     http://localhost:3000/auth/signup
Headers: Content-Type: application/json
Body (JSON):
{
  "name": "Sarah Parent",
  "email": "sarah@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "role": "parent"
}
✅ Expected: 201 — copy the token from the response

2. Sign Up as a Mentor
Method:  POST
URL:     http://localhost:3000/auth/signup
Headers: Content-Type: application/json
Body (JSON):
{
  "name": "John Mentor",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "role": "mentor"
}
✅ Expected: 201 — copy the mentor's token too

3. Login
Method:  POST
URL:     http://localhost:3000/auth/login
Headers: Content-Type: application/json
Body (JSON):
{
  "email": "sarah@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}
✅ Expected: 200 with a fresh token

4. Get My Profile
Method:  GET
URL:     http://localhost:3000/auth/me
Headers: Authorization: Bearer <parent_token>
✅ Expected: 200 with your user object

5. Create a Student (use parent token)
Method:  POST
URL:     http://localhost:3000/students
Headers: Content-Type: application/json
         Authorization: Bearer <parent_token>
Body (JSON):
{
  "name": "Tommy",
  "age": 10,
  "grade": "5th"
}
✅ Expected: 201 — copy the student _id

6. Get All Students (use parent token)
Method:  GET
URL:     http://localhost:3000/students
Headers: Authorization: Bearer <parent_token>
✅ Expected: 200 with list of your students

7. Create a Lesson (use mentor token)
Method:  POST
URL:     http://localhost:3000/lessons
Headers: Content-Type: application/json
         Authorization: Bearer <mentor_token>
Body (JSON):
{
  "title": "Intro to Algebra",
  "description": "Learn the basics of variables and equations"
}
✅ Expected: 201 — copy the lesson _id

8. Get All Lessons
Method:  GET
URL:     http://localhost:3000/lessons
Headers: Authorization: Bearer <parent_token>
✅ Expected: 200 with all lessons

9. Book a Student into a Lesson (use parent token)
Method:  POST
URL:     http://localhost:3000/bookings
Headers: Content-Type: application/json
         Authorization: Bearer <parent_token>
Body (JSON):
{
  "studentId": "<student _id from step 5>",
  "lessonId":  "<lesson _id from step 7>"
}
✅ Expected: 201 with booking details

10. Get All Bookings (use parent token)
Method:  GET
URL:     http://localhost:3000/bookings
Headers: Authorization: Bearer <parent_token>
✅ Expected: 200 with your bookings

11. Create a Session (use mentor token)
Method:  POST
URL:     http://localhost:3000/sessions
Headers: Content-Type: application/json
         Authorization: Bearer <mentor_token>
Body (JSON):
{
  "lessonId": "<lesson _id from step 7>",
  "date": "2025-09-01T10:00:00Z",
  "topic": "Chapter 1 — Variables",
  "summary": "Students learned what variables are."
}
✅ Expected: 201 — copy the session _id

12. Get Sessions for a Lesson
Method:  GET
URL:     http://localhost:3000/lessons/<lesson_id>/sessions
Headers: Authorization: Bearer <parent_token>
✅ Expected: 200 with list of sessions

13. Join a Session (use parent token — bonus)
Method:  POST
URL:     http://localhost:3000/sessions/<session_id>/join
Headers: Content-Type: application/json
         Authorization: Bearer <parent_token>
Body (JSON):
{
  "studentId": "<student _id from step 5>"
}
✅ Expected: 200 — student added to session attendees

14. LLM Summarize
Method:  POST
URL:     http://localhost:3000/llm/summarize
Headers: Content-Type: application/json
         Authorization: Bearer <parent_token>
Body (JSON):
{
  "text": "Photosynthesis is the process by which green plants use sunlight, water and carbon dioxide to produce oxygen and energy in the form of sugar. It occurs mainly in leaves, in the chloroplasts, using the green pigment chlorophyll. The light reactions occur in the thylakoid membranes while the Calvin cycle takes place in the stroma."
}
